patch.comment: Include CHANGELOG.md in published releases again
Include missing `type` modifiers on type-only exports.
Only emit an error about unsupported library types if the public path is actually used.

minor.comment: Add a second exported plugin (`SetPublicPathCurrentScriptPlugin`) that creates a wrapper around the runtime chunk and uses the `document.currentScript` API to get the current script's URL.

major.comment: Update the plugin to work with Webpack 5 and drop support for Webpack 4.

patch.comment: Fix line endings in published package.
Update type-only imports to include the type modifier.

major.comment: Emit an error on Webpack 5 instead of a warning and remove the optional peerDependency on Webpack.

patch.comment: Move webpack version detection logic to the "@rushstack/webpack-plugin-utilities" package
Update typings to only import from "webpack."

minor.comment: Introduce a warning when running in Webpack 5.

patch.comment: Update the package.json repository field to include the directory property.
Upgrade the `@types/node` dependency to version to version 12.

minor.comment: Remove uglify dependency and make suffix script always minified.

patch.comment: Updated project to build with Heft
Fix an issue where sourcemaps with inlined sources can contain incorrect escaping.
PACKAGE NAME CHANGE: The NPM scope was changed from `@microsoft/set-webpack-public-path-plugin` to `@rushstack/set-webpack-public-path-plugin`

minor.comment: Add functionality to use the webpack-produced asset name to find the loaded acript.

patch.comment: Republish all packages in web-build-tools to resolve GitHub issue #782

minor.comment: Include an option to skip chunk and asset detection.

major.comment: Update the plugin to support Webpack 4.

minor.comment: Adding new option to ISetWebpackPublicPathOptions, called findLast

patch.comment: Locked down some "@types/" dependency versions to avoid upgrade conflicts
Force a patch bump in case the previous version was an empty package

patch.comment: Deprecate @types/es6-coll ections in favor of built-in typescript typings 'es2015.collection' a nd 'es2015.iterable'

minor.comment: Add a new getPostProcessScript configuration option to allow consumers to do arbitrary post-processing on the webpack public path variable.
